Old Forts of the Great Lakes
Thunder Bay Press | 1994 | ISBN: 1882376056 | English | 180 pages | PDF | 25.6 MB

For two centuries the Great Lakes region was a violent one. From the time the French arrived in the early 1600s and allied themselves with some of the Indian nations in their wars against other Indian nations, until at least a generation after the War of 1812, people felt safest when they were in or near fortified places
